The paper deals with the design of energy-efficient wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of graph-based signal processing techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also deals with the optimization of power consumption, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of sparsity priors suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
